Summary: The player meets SAM COE and his daughter CORA COE. The three of them travel to Akila City, the capital of the Freestar Collective. Sam tries to retrieve maps left behind by his legendary ancestor, Solomon. But Sam's father, JACOB COE, has gotten to the maps first and demands to talk face to face. After arguing with his dad, Sam and the player find a way to retrieve the maps from Jacob. They then travel to Akila's dangerous frontier, and have to get past the LOCKE gang, an outlaw group, before finally finding the Artifact.

Sarah Morgan takes the player with her as she investigates a lead on an Artifact. The player meets John Savea, the UC Vanguard recruiting officer, who points you and Sarah to a Vanguard volunteer on Cydonia, Mars. You investigate, and find that the Vanguard went missing patrolling "the Old Neighborhood" - the Sol System. Patrol the planets of Venus, Jupiter, and Saturn with Sarah. Find the missing Vanguard and rescue them.

The player meets VLADIMIR SALL, a Constellation member who lives onboard the Eye, a starstation. Vladimir explains how Constellation tracks down the Artifacts and sends the player out to find more of them in the fringes of space. On returning, the player talks to MATTEO and NOEL about the Artifact hunts before being summoned back to the Eye to look at some larger space anomalies with Vladimir. The player investigates an anomaly only to discover a large, alien temple with an elaborate puzzle sequence. A light engulfs the player in the center of the temple and they gain powers, which they demonstrate to Constellation on their return.

The player returns to Vectera, looking for BARRETT, but ends up finding LIN alone at the mining colony. Pirates came back to the colony and Barrett and HELLER were taken captive. The player tracks their ship down, only to find it crash landed, with Heller alone and injured. He explains that he and Barrett managed to get away from the pirates but ended up crashing the ship. He then points you to the pirate's base, where Barrett is being held by the pirate captain MATSURA.

The player has some time to discuss the fate of Infinity LTD with Ryujin board members. Due to what the player has learned, each outcome will have negatives and positives that they'll need to weigh. Depending on previous choices, they may also have the ability to sway the Board on keeping Masako as CEO and shelving Project Dominion, aka the Internal Neuroamp.

The player gets to attend their first board meeting where the truth about the mole and Masako's plans for Infinity LTD revealed. With the Internal Neuroamp completed, the player finally gets it implanted with the opportunity to test it out. Afterwards, they meet back up with Masako in her office where they are briefed on the plan. The player is given a special "Overseer" program to run on Lucas Drexler and Faye Sengsavahn's computers in order to wipe all references to Ryujin and Project Dominion, while at the same time collecting evidence for Infinity's crimes: unathorized human trials at the Clinic, and hiring mercenaries to take out the innocent workers at CM Station RC-1. Finally, the player will grab the final prototype that Infinity has as the last piece of evidence that Project Dominion ever existed. Before they can return to Ryujin, they need to drop off the slate with the evidence on it at SSNN, ensuring David Barron's interest is peaked so the story will be sure to air. Once the player returns to Masako at Ryujin Tower, they'll listen to the broadcast together which may or may not be in Masako's favor.

The player's directed to a derelict space ship to collect some rare liquor by "Betting Lizzy," Gagarin's sole bartender. The player has to traverse a ship in mid-flight that is having its gravity actively switched on and off while fighting pirates, then return with the booze to Lizzy.

The player has agreed to help Helena find her company's missing data. She suspects one of her employees - Bonifac Maksimov - and sends the player to a nearby planet to find him. The player find him there, kidnapped, and the two confront his kidnapped - Simon Maldonado - who makes the player an offer: let me keep the stolen data in exchange for a hefty payment. The player has to either kille Maldonado or Bonifac before returning to Helena to report what happened.

As a newly-recruited Deputy in the respected Freestar Rangers, the player is carrying out an investigation into a mercenary company called The First that's been threatening farmers in an effort to seize their land for some unknown purpose. The player tracked the First to their hideout and confronted their leader, Major Paxton Hull, who revealed the true architect of the conspiracy, HopeTech founder and president Ron Hope. Now the player is going to confront Hope in his starshio factory to learn the nature of his plans, and bring him to justice one way or another.

They run into Ecliptic mercenaries, hired by Infinity LTD and learn the shipment was sent to the Clinic. At the Clinic they'll retrieve the shipment and can learn just how far Infinity LTD has been willing to go to complete their own version of the internal neuroamp.

They find her ready and waiting at the Seokga Syndicate hideout where they can determine her fate. She claims Ularu Chen has set her up and is the ultimate person behind everything. The player can believe her and take the evidence she has against Ularu, or they kill her. As a newly-recruited Deputy in the respected Freestar Rangers, the player is carrying out an investigation into a mercenary company called The First that's been threatening farmers in an effort to seize their land for some unknown purpose. The player has learned the identity of a highly-placed member of the First named Maya Cruz, who is known to be a technical genius and expert with computers. Cruz recently had a medical emergency of some kind and needed surgery, but the player does not know the details.

At the suggestion of Marshal Daniel Blake, leader of the Freestar Rangers, the player has come to the Clinic, a sophisticated medical research facility and hospital, in hopes of finding Maya Cruz there. Ranger Ben Armistead, an old-fashioned salt-of-the-earth type, is stationed there and helps the player get the lay of the land. After some investigative work, the player tracks Maya Cruz to her asteroid hideout, which is beset with traps and killer robots, before finally confronting her.

As a newly-recruited Deputy in the respected Freestar Rangers, the player is carrying out an investigation into a mercenary company called The First that's been threatening farmers in an effort to seize their land for some unknown purpose. The player has learned the identity of a highly-placed member of the First named Marco Graziani, who is known to come from a family of wealthy criminal smugglers and might be bankrolling the First. \n\nMarshal Blake, leader of the Freestar Rangers, sends the playerto the infamous gambling den known as Red Mile, where patrons bet on a deadly game of survival. There, Ranger Autumn MacMillan has been trying to crack a smuggling ring and might be able to help the player track down Marco. After the player is forced to run the deadly red mile, the lethal gauntlet that gives the cantina its name, the establishment's owner sets up a meeting with Marco and the player confronts the mercenary smuggler, ultimately obtaining an encrypted slate that can help to expose the First's plans.
This quest contains the scene and support dialogue for Hadrian learning that her father, the war criminal Vae Victis, is still alive.

The player is sent to speak and meet with Dalton Fiennes, Ryujin Industries Chief Security Officer. Dalton tells the player he and Masako are enacting Security Directive Theta. This means that every single Ryujin employee is going to be fully investigated by a third party company. The only "exception" to this is Ularu Chen who requires special attention due to her own skills as an ex-operative and current Chief Operations Officer. Because Ularu would be so good at covering any tracks, Dalton has contractd out a man named Nyx, the best hacker in the Settled Systems and the only one to ever breach Ryujin Security. Nyx is going to give the player a program to run on Ularu's computer, but the catch is that no one, not even Ryujin's own security can know this investigation is going on... so the player needs to infiltrate Ryujin Tower. Dalton informs the player their keycard will not be good during this time and any guards will consider them to be trespassing. He warns against killing any of the guards and arms the player with a Disurptor, a non-lethal weapon. He also says he'll ensure all non-essential personnel have left the building, so only the security guards will be there. The player infiltrates Ryujin through a vent system and does their best to avoid the guards, running Nyx's program on Ularu's computer and potentially that of another, Camden Cho. Once complete, the player returns to Nyx who analyzes the information and puts anything pertinent on a new slate for Dalton. The player returns to Dalton at a now normal Ryujin Tower where he quickly sees the evidence points to Imogene Salzo.

The player has discovered evidence that Vae Victis knows about the Lazarus Plant. They return to MAST to confront him and he reveals the truth - he organized the attacks on New Atlantis and Tau Ceti. He requests the player lie for him, however, and tell everyone it was soley Orlase - the Warlock - who triggered the attacks.

The player can then report what they uncovered to Hadrian and Percival - or lie to them - and then proceeds to share what they found with the Cabinet - or lie to them too.

The quest then finishes with two other major decisions - how to handle the discovery of the Lazarus plant (destroy it, share knowledge of it, etc.) and how to handle the Terrormorphs - by deploying the Aceles or a microbe.

Hadrian and Percial have formed a plan on how to stop the Terrormorphs - remove them from human worlds by either hunting them down using creatures called "Aceles" or wiping them out with a microbe. In order to prove out either plan, though, they'll need some raw materials. And the place to collect those - Londinion.\n\nThe player, Hadrian, Percival, and Kaiser head to Londinion to collect those materials, but discover a plant - the Lazarus Plant - that might've been used to trigger the attacks on New Atlantis and Tau Ceti. The player and Hadrian then discover a lead to who might've known about the plant - Hadrian's father, Vae Victis.
Peter Brennan is a clueless corporate executive. Here, he mistakes one of the newer employees, Gilly, for his personal assistant. She corrects him, and he plays it off as no big deal.
Two marines talking. One is feeling sort from yesterday's training, but the other makes sure to remind them that that kind of undisciplined talk can get everyone in trouble.

Trevor, the Mining boss approaches one of his employees, Laylah, who has been messing with the programming of the company's beloved mining robot companion. She fesses up, and he tells her it's okay, just tone it down a bit. She agrees to this.

Samund, an ex-con who's been working the mines for many years is coming to Joy for some spiritual guidance, but he's not very religious, so when Horus, a representativ eof the Sanctum Universum butts in to help, he politely declines and decides to leave, instead.
Renee comes up to Taye and asks him to "guess what," like kids do. He makes a few wrong guesses, then Renee surprises him with something she made for him: a drawing or some other craft.

Gauir passes by Noam, who has something to tell her about Laylah taking some of her explosives. This concerns Gauri, but she also knows Laylah often pulls pranks like this, so maybe she's just messing with her?  Think of Naom as a robot version of Alexa or Siri.
Laylah often pulls pranks on the other miners. Gauri decides to get Laylah back, and Laylah almost buys it. It's a friendly exchange.
Booth, the chief security officer in Cydonia, is following up with Jack, the bartender, about an incident he heard about. Just checking in. Jack is tough, he can handle it.

Typical office chatter. Leona notices that Gilly hasn't been her normal self recently so she asks what's wrong. Tia blurts out that Gilly is going through a divorce, much to Gilly's shock. She chastises Tia, but Leona says she already knew. Gilly says she'll be fine, and Leona offers to invite her on a getaway to help her forget about her problems.

Ship Combat lines for unique NPCs

Summary: Abe Levitz, the cabin manager on board an old colony ship, the ECS constant has asked the player to track down his crew's relatives after finding out the ship was not alone in the universe as they previously thought. The player finds the relatives and delivers the news, but the relative is skeptical, and so it is up to the player to convince them and report back to Abe.
Just a misc quest to let the player speak to Abe and accept or decline doing the actual quest.

after helping the colony ship ECS Constant, the player also helped one of its crew members, Janet Yang, who was unhappy with the resolution. There are two potential scenarios: either the ECS Constant resettled the colonists at Paradiso, or they''re drifting in space, looking for a new planet to call home. In either case, the player has helped Janet escape her situation. Now, the player is in New Atlantis, when they hear a familiar voice call out to them, and Janet rushes over to find them. Janet is asking the player to deliver a letter to her sister, Julia, who stayed with the rest of the ECS Constant Crew.

When the colony ship ECS Constant arrived at its destination prior to this quest, they found it already inhabited, dashing their plans of colonizing it. The player helped by outfiting the ship with a grav drive so it can find a new home world. However, the captain of the ship, Diana Brackenridge, is determined to find the perfect world, as close to the original as possible. This makes Janet Yang upset, because she is sick of this ship and deserately wants to leave after finding out that there are other people out there. The player offers to help convince the captain to let her go.

The player has helped the colony ship, ECs Constant resettle at a luxury resort, Paradiso. The colonists have entered into a contract with the Paradiso Group to pay for their resettlement there by going into debt, requiring them to work for the resort to pay it off before they can leave. Janet is particularly upset about this deal and wants to get out of here. The player offers to negotiate for her debt to be forgiven so she can leave.

The player has finished their work with Vae Victis, learning the location of one of Hadrian's old team members - Kaiser - as well as the fact that Hadrian is both a clone of Vae Victis, and the fact that the old Admiral is still alive.

The player can tell Hadrian what they've discovered, and she'll request the player head to Niira to recover Kaiser.

There, the player meets Gel, prioreitor of the only business on Niira - 1-Of-A-Kind Salvage - which makes their money chopping up mechs and selling off the parts.

He can help the player find Kaiser, who has run out of power stalking a dangerous Xenoweapon known as Unit 99. Once the player restores Kaiser (either by purchasing a battery from Gel or making one themselves), they'll help Kaiser "disarm" Unit 99, by either killing the alien or wiping its mind control interface. 

Once Unit 99 has been dealt with, Kaiser and the player return to Mars, where they'll learn their next destination - Londinion.

Holds the dialogue for the Trackers Alliance Agents. The player can ask them about work, and they will point the player to the nearest Mission Board which lists Bounty Hunting jobs. The player can also ask other questions.
The player aks a Trackers Alliance Agent about where to find Bounty Hunting jobs, and is directed to the nearest Mission Board, which has such jobs.

The player has asked a Trade Authority vendor about working for the Trade Authority. They point the player to the nearest Mission Board. The player completes this quest when accepting a Trade Authority mission.

The player takes a tour of New Homestead with Bill Stasap of Starsap Tours. He will tell them facts about the settlement along the way, and stop at each point of interest to allow the player to ask questions.

Luthor Atlanta manages the Chunks in New Homestead. Since this is kind of in the boondocks of the Settled Systems, they don't get new stock as often as some of the other Chunks, and this particular location seems to run out of Chunks Special sauce frequently (Luthor may or may not have something to do with that). The player can offer to help Luthor by picking some more sauce up from another Chunks location and bring it back to him.

Dr. Giuliana Lakota is one of a few New Homestead citizens who does not like the tourists who come to her home town to gawk at them and their relatively simple life. She sespecially dislikes them because they tend not to be careful while out on their tours, and frequently end up in her doctor's office, which sometimes prevents her from seeing her regular patients. She's hatched a plan to scare them off by pretending to be an alien creature, having ordered a custom-made monster costume, but she's been too busy to put it on and use it to scare the tourists. This is where the player comes in to help her out. This quest is repeatable.

Brownouts are plaguing New Homestead because the wind turbines keep icing up. Joyce Osaka is fairly new to New Homestead, but she's determined to fix these problems. However, she could use some help from the player until the replacement parts come in to fix the problem permanantly. She asks the player to go out and de-ice the equipment. This is a repeatable quest.

Full: [LC088 - Crimson Fleet Final Battle - Space Battle]
Matters of the Hart Space Encounter

Summary: Jane Weller owns a small independent general good shop in Cydonia. She pulled herself up by her bootstraps all by herslef and made it work despite the difficulties she faced in her life. Everything was going well: shop's doing well, enough so that she could afford a cargo ship to help expand her operations. There's just one problem. She bought her ship, the Berry Mule, from a sketchy dealer, and it turns out the ship was stolen. Now, her pilot friend has gone missing with the ship. she asks the player to help track it down and get it back, but the player finds it has been reclaimed by Ecliptic mercenaries, who are intent on bringing it back to its rightful owner. The player can choose how to get it back and save Erick in a tense standoff with the mercs.

After the player proves themselves as being trustworthy, Denis Averin has another mission for them. Denis hears about various renegade groups throughout the Settled Systems, and asks the player to retreive valuable weaponry and other equipment so that he can refurbish and resell it to his own customers on the side.

After helping Trevor Petyarre with his request for new mining equipment, Gilly Seong, a psychologist working for Deimos,  reveals that she knew the player was up to something. However, instead of ratting them out, she asks for their aid, trusting that they will be eager to help. She is behind in her tasks to get psychological evaluations to Deimos employees, so she asks the player to deliver them for her. The player will deliver and collect them from various employees, learning a little bit about them in the process.
This quest handles dialogue when a Mini Bot is activated.

Full: This is the tagging system for the Neon Gang quests

Summary:
The player happens upon Rivkah Ovadia (RIV-kah o-VAh-dee-ah), who is ill with some sort of respiratory issue. After asking about it, she informs the player that she can't get help because she is currently Wanted by her father after attacking him and stealing his spaceship, hinting that their relationship was toxic and she did it to escape. She wants to try to repair that relationship with him, but knows that he put a bounty on her and has been trying to track her down ever since.

The player offers to help, and she tells him to bring him a bottle of his favorite whiskey as a peace offering form her.

When the player confronts her father, Natan (Nah-TAHN), he is distrustful, stubborn, and aggressive. The player may take one of several approaches which can bring him to his senses, or escalate the situation. The player then returns to Rivkah to tell her what transpired, or, they can side with Natan and turn in Rivkah.

The player's search for one of the final Artifacts leads them to Nishina Research Station, a remote research outpost near the edge of the settled systems. Once inside, they find themselves shifting between two universes: one where the station is intact and inhabited, and the other where it has been destroyed in a catastrophic fire, leaving only one survivor. The player must navigate the shifting, gain control of the phenomenon, and shift back and forth between universes to claim the Artifact.\n\nThis quest, SE_MQ207C, is the distress signal that plays from the satellite when the player first arrives in orbit above Nishina.

The eccentric manager of the Cydonia UC Exchange, Denis Averin, needs help finding his ship, which unexpectedly landed out in the Mars desert. He's unsure what happened, but suspects a problem on board. He wants the player to investigate because local authorities are taking too long and he needs the shipment ASAP.
Sets up a group around the main center marker, allows all creature aliases. This is a very general Template and can be refined further.

Full: Cora's dialogue when Sam is a companion

Summary: MUST RUN ON START

The player has managed to approve Trevor's request for new mining equipment. Trevor tells the player that one of his employees, Hank Ferraro, left to go get the equipment as soon as the request came through. It should have been a quick trip, but Hank hasn't returned yet. Trevor asks the player to follow up and try to find out what they can, first by inquiring about hank at Cydonia Ship Services. They learn that Hank has returned to Mars, but didn't land at port like expected. The player then finds out that Hank stole the goods and must confront him to get them back. They can choose to kill Hank, or talk him out of his misdeeds, at which point they may choose to turn him in to security or cover for him. In any case, they will succeed at getting the equipment back.

Trevor Petyarre is trying to improve the working conditions for the miners in Cydonia. They've been using broken and outdated equipment for too long, and his request fro new equipment has fallen through the corporate cracks. He asks the player to help him with an elaborate plan to get the request approved. The player is to ensure they get hired as the Mining Operations Executive's new assistant, so they can gain access to his computer and approve the request for Peter, but first, they need to jump through a few hoops.

The player has gotten the Exective Assistant job and must report to Peter Brennan. This is all in an effort to help Trevor Petyarre and the miners. Trevor has submitted a request for new mining equipment to Peter. The player must get access to Peter's computer and approve the request, because Peter can't do anything without his assistant doing it for him. But first, Peter needs the player to go get a shipment he's waiting for. The player finds that the Governor of Cydonia, Glen Hurst, has held Peter's shipment, and requires the player to take care of a problem for him before he'll release the shipment. The player tracks down Hurst's ship and either destroys it, or finds out the truth behind Hurst's intentions. Either way, they'll be able to return with the package to Brennan, and finish their task.
This is a random conversation that can start up in the background as the player wanders around Gagarin. In it, local recruiter Vanguard Zinaida Kupers speaks to a local citizen.

This is a random conversation that can start up in the background as the player wanders around Gagarin. In it, UC Security Chief Dalisto Pretorius chats with her friend, Doctor Pauline Keala, in the local clinic.

This is a random conversation that can start up in the background as the player wanders around Gagarin. In it, Helena Strickland, head of Reliant Medical on Gagarin, summons her junior exec, Bonifac Maksimov, into her office for a request.

This is a random conversation that can start up in the background as the player wanders around Gagarin. In it, head of Gagarin's local Arc Might facility, Lawan Ariesen gets a report from her trusty robot coworker in her office.

Mitch Benjamin is unable to leave his home due to some sort of medical condition. So, when the player comes along and offers to help him out, Mitch takes the opportunity to send the player out to get some first editions of his favorite book series, Dragonstar Force. When the player returns, Mitch is elated. This quest can be repeated up to 30 times, once for each book in the series.

A bored little girl, Renee Shelby, asks the player to help her out since she isn't allowed to leave her condo complex. She wants to spread some joy around Cydonia by putting up cute pictures of a character she made, called Space Frog from Outer Space.

New Homestead is a "Living History" community. Think Plymouth Plantation, or certain ccommunities in Amish country. It was originally a xenobiology research facility in the days before grav drive travel. Then, it transitioned into an off-world colony research facility after no significant alien life was found. Now, people just live here, preserving early colonial traditions and such. It serves as a tourist destination, and people come here because it's one of the closest communities to old Earth in the Sol system, the cradle of humanity.

Samund checks his messages with Noam, and finds that someone has left him a threatening one anonymously. He's pretty sure who it is though, and threatens them via Noam.  Think of Naom as a robot version of Alexa or Siri.

Tia, the HR director for Deimos Staryards, is asking Leona, the Corporate Liason, leona, if her request for an assistant was approved. Leona tells her than nothing's happened yet, but continue being patient. Though, she also wonders if Tia is having trouble with her workload, and Tia is quick to dismiss that idea so she doesn't look replaceable.

Two marines discuss the Red Devils possibly coming back. The Red Devils are a specialized elite military force, like the Navy Seals. They've been disbanded for a while now, but the program may be starting up again soon. Naturally, one of the marines believes they'd make the cut.
A patron orders a drink at the Broken Spear bar after a long day. Jack, the bartender obliges.

Two of the old-timer miners discuss retirement. Samund has no intention of retiring anytime soon, but Andres misses his family, who live off-world. He's been dragging his feet on it, but he's starting to change his mind and wants to go home.

Laylah is fiercely competetive. She's trying to goad Gauri into taking a bet that she'll be able to produce more ore than her, but Gauri, as a manager, has access to some of the current numbers, so she's confident that she's ahead, much to Laylah's surprise.
Taye walks over to Renee, and renee asks him if he wants to play 20 questions. Taye indulges her, even though she often thinks of a bunny. Naturally, he guesses it pretty easily.

Horus, a representative of the Sanctum Universum, a theist spiritual organization, is asking his colleague Joy, a representative of the Enlightened, a human-centric atheist spiritual organization, to go for drinks after work. They have a history of getting into heated, yet friendly debates when drinks are involved.
Hank is kind of a meathead. Here, he's boasting about some big hunk of ore he pulled up, but it's doubtful that he actually did it. It's the proverbial fish that got away. Rivkah doesn't buy it.

One Marine to another. The first one wonders if they'll be seeing any real combat action anytime soon, but the second one took this assignment specifically because it didn't seem likely that there would be any.
Taye's mother has been depressed since his father died. In this scene, he goes to try to comfort her.
Laylah is leaving a message with Noam, the company's assistant robot. noam misunderstands her request and this upsets her. Think of Naom as a robot version of Alexa or Siri.

The player's presence is requested by Vae Victis, the once-executed, now jailed former Admiral of the UC. Vae Victis has a proposal for the player - he'll give the player the location of Hadrian's Xenowarfare team if the player will kill someone for him. The player can either agree to help or offer to bring the criminal in question - Dr. Reginald Orlase - to justice. \n\nThey're directed to The Den to speak to the local Vanguard, then out to an old debris field where Orlase has been hiding. After a dogfight where they can either destory Orlase's ship, killing the doctor, or board it and he'll do the job himself, and the collect his ID to return to Vae Victis, completing the task.

Cydonia, on Mars, is the first major planetary colony in the Settled Systems, first established by the Deimos Staryards corporation. It's still heavily influenced by their mining operations, but now formally under the United Colonies banner. Much of the population here are transient miners who work for a set of years on a highly profitble contract basis, then move on, but there are some permanent locals as well. It's formeost an industrial city, with a mining town/industrial vibe. Like a Pittsburgh, or a Detroit. It's old and run down, with few frills and not a lot to do, but it's still a healthy, somewhat prosperous community. There's also a strong military presence here, where UC Marines train.

The PLAYER completes the Armillary and can now enter the Unity. They can speak to their companions and other members of Constellation before they go. When they arrive at the Unity, the player meets a version of themself who explains the Unity's rules: you can enter it completely and be reborn in the multiverse as a Starborn, or you can leave and return to your universe.
Go on a radiant mission to take out an operative for a competing company or an agent who went rogue at Ryujin, but a no-kill option will be available.
The PLAYER leaves Earth, only to see that the HUNTER and the EMISSARY have are waiting in orbit. They each ask the player to side with them against the other. A fight in space is inevitable.

Full: First to Fight, First to Die
Summary: As a newly-recruited Deputy in the respected Freestar Rangers, the player is carrying out an investigation into a mercenary company called The First that's been threatening farmers in an effort to seize their land for some unknown purpose. The player has finally learned the location of the First's hideout, and can now confrnot them head-on, which means going toe-to-toe with their leader, disgraced former war hero Paxton Hull.
The player returns from meeting the Starborn (MQ207) and tells Constellation what they're learned about the Unity. VLADIMIR SALL gives the player the final Artifacts that the Eye has discovered.

The player's search for one of the final Artifacts leads them to Nishina Research Station, a remote research outpost near the edge of the settled systems. Once inside, they find themselves shifting between two universes: one where the station is intact and inhabited, and the other where it has been destroyed in a catastrophic fire, leaving only one survivor. The player must navigate the shifting, gain control of the phenomenon, and shift back and forth between universes to claim the Artifact.\n\nThis quest, MQ207C, has the bulk of the dialogue for the actual quest.
This is a StartsGameEnabled quest to support location reservation on game start and other systemic LD functionality that needs to remain available at all times.

MATTEO KHATRI tells the player that, during the Hunter's attack, he mentioned the word "Unity." This word has significance to Matteo's religion, the Sanctum Universum. He asks the player to come with him to meet KEEPER AQUILUS, the reglion's founder, to see if the word has hidden meaning. Aquilus tells the player to speak to all the faiths, not just his own, to uncover the word's true meaning.

The ECS Constant is a colony ship that left earth before grav drives were invented, and humanity has sort of leap-frogged over them. During their nearly 200 year journey, generations were born, lived, and died on the ship, and strangely, their course took them nowhere near any other civilization, so they were never discovered, and long forgotten. Now, they face a problem: the planet they set out for is inhabited by a settlement called Paradiso, a fancy resort. There's a communication issue, so the player needs to go between the two parties and negotiate . Unfortunately, no solution is perfectly ideal, so the player must make a difficult choice in how to help resolve the situation.

A helper quest to start MS06 when the player arrives in the Porrima II Orbit. The player will get a message broadcast to their ship telling them to speak with Security Chief Jiro Sugiyama in Paradiso, concerning a sensitive matter: There's a strange ship orbitting Porrima II, and he need someone to help with it.

Paradiso is the ultimate resort getaway on the planet Porrima II at the fringes of the Settled Systems. It's a privately owned planet, not affiliated with the United Colonies or the Freestar Collective. As such, they get away with some pretty shady practices, but they generally do a good job of hiding them from the public. Everything about the planet seems too perfect to be true, from the weather, to the beaches, to the wildlife. The resort staff all know each other. Most of the executive board spends more time on the beach than in the boardroom. Recently, a giant mysterious ship has appeared in orbit, and the board is freaking out, and doing their best to hide it from the resort guests. In reality, this ship is a 200 year old colony ship that has just arrived from its long pre-grav drive journey from Earth, and they feel they have a claim to the planet.

This qusest holds all the dialogue for the settlement of Gagarin, a large settlement in UC space. Gagarin was once an industrial power house - churning out large mechanized combat platforms (or "Mechs), but when mechs were banned after the Colony War, Gagarin went into a steep decline. Now some businesses have decided to return to Gagarin, buying up the old buildings for cheap, which has led to much debate among the locals.

As a newly-recruited Deputy in the respected Freestar Rangers, the player is carrying out an investigation into a mercenary company called The First that's been threatning farmers in an effort to seize their land for some unknown purpose. The trail has led to the pleasure city of Neon, where the player has come in search of a starship thief who brazenly stole a ship right out of the HopeTech factory and delivered it to a group of First mercenaries. The thief might be able to provide some answers about what the First is up to.\n\nFirst, the player meets with Neon's jaded and pragmatic Ranger, Jaylen Pryce. Ranger Pryce takes the player to meet maintenance worker Billy Clayton, an informant who keeps an eye on the ship traffic traveling to and from the city. Billy saw the stolen ship, but asks the player to intervene on his behalf with a loan shark that's trying to collect money that Billy's dead brother owed him. After learning the thief's identity, Ranger Pryce joins the player in confronting her at Madame Sauvage's, a nightclub. The thief, Grace Early, gives the names of two highly-placed members of the First.
The player encounters a pilot flying the sensible ship they designed for MS05.
The player encounters a pilot flying the ridiculous ship they designed in MS05.

Full: A Tree Grows in New Atlantis

Summary: This is the base settlement dialogue for the ECS Constant, a colony ship that left Earth before grav drives were invented, so they have taken almost 200 years to reach their destination, only to find out that it has already been colonized. The NPCs here can be in one of three states: on board the ship in orbit above the resort settlement Paradiso, resettled in Paradiso, or remaining on their ship and still searching for a new home out in space. Their dialogue will change to reflect these states.

As a Freestar Ranger trainee, the player has returned from Montara Luna, where they partnered with Ranger Helga Dubray to confront a gang of thugs that were trying to intimidate a farmer off her land. To the player's surprise, the thugs turned out ot be well-armed mercenaries traveling in a stolen HopeTech ship. Now the player reports to Marshal Blake for a debriefing, investigates the mercenaries and then travels to Polve, where HopeTech's HQ and ship factory are located and where the ship was stolen. Working with the local ranger, Nia Kalu, the player meets with HopeTech CEO and founder Ron Hope to learn about the starship theft.

The player's search for one of the final Artifacts leads them to Nishina Research Station, a remote research outpost near the edge of the settled systems. Once inside, they find themselves shifting between two universes: one where the station is intact and inhabited, and the other where it has been destroyed in a catastrophic fire, leaving only one survivor. The player must navigate the shifting, gain control of the phenomenon, and shift back and forth between universes to claim the Artifact.

This quest, MQ207C_Support, includes dialogue that needs to be available when the primary quest (MQ206D) is not running.
 - MQ207C_110_EntranceIntercom is the initial interaction with the intercom outside the station.
 - The _Main dialogues are the topics the player can ask about late in the quest, or after the quest has ended.

This quest holds all the dialogue for the Eleos Retreat, a facility that's actively being built to act as a growth and rehabilitation center for the galaxy's incarcerated. When the player arrive, however, all work on the Retreat has come to a stop. The player slowly figures out why (one of the construction workers has been kidnapped and the rest refuse to work) and manages to fix their problems (uncovering a plot by a couple of bounty hunters who have been harassing the crew and staff of the retreat, and confronting them).

After making an impression on Marshal Daniel Blake by stepping in to help resolve a hostage situation at GalBank in Akila City, the player joins the Freestar Rangers as a trainee. In this capacity, the player joins Ranger Helga Dubray as she responds to a call for help from a farm on Montara Luna, a moon in the Cheyenne system. There, the player meets a farmer named Mikaela Waggoner who's being threatened by a band of thugs that want to take possession of her farm. The player and Ranger Dubray track the thugs through a winding canyon infested with dangerous wildlife before engaging in a shootout at the thugs' camp. A clue aboard the thugs' ship points to a larger conspiracy at work.
This is the base settlement dialogue for Crucible.

Stroud-Eklund Shipyards is having difficulty with their latest project. No one can agree on anything, and production has stalled. Walter Stroud has asked the player to step in and try to get production back on track by going to the staryard and working with his R&D team. They face a number of problems ranging from budget concerns, requiring more market research data, and interpersonal issues. The player will solve these issues, and a ship will be built based on the decisions they made.

In this, the first quest of the Freestar Collective faction quest line, the player has arrived in Akila City for the first time and is stopped at the gate by a guard who warns of a hostage situation playing out at the local branch of GalBank. The player volunteers to help and meets Marshal Daniel Blake, head of the renowned Freestar Rangers. Working with Marshal Blake, the player can either try to persuade the bank robbers to surrender or infiltrate the bank and take them out with lethal force. Marshal Blake is impressed and offers the player the opportunity to join the Freestar Rangers, which leads into the next quest in the chain.

Hadrian has sent the player to Mars to give have her former colleague, Jakob, look at the sample of the anamolous Terrormorph sample. The player arrives to find the Jakob's gone missing due to a debt. The player, working with the local miners hiding Jakob, can either pay off the debt or find a way to get the local mines restarted in order to find Jakob.\n\nOnce the player does, he confirms Hadrian's fears - this Terrormorph could be a sign of things to come. But Hadrian has a plan. Get their old research from the Armistice Archives and put together a plan to stop the Terrormorphs for good.

Ularu Chen has completely bought into the player by now and wants to meet them. She sends the player to meet up with one of her contacts, Simon Ryczek, who has a lead that she may find valuable. After gaining information from Simon, the player breaks into an office in Cydonia to steal the information and bring it back to Chen. Chen realizes it's for Project Dominion and takes this information to Masako Imada, Ryujin's CEO, to discuss the new info. The only answer is that there must be a mole within the company.
Go on a mission for Imogene Salzo to steal something from Trident Luxury Lines, a competitor of one of Ryujin's subsidiaries, Taiyo Astroneering.

The player has been tasked with convincing the Ambassadors of the Freestar Collective and House Va'ruun to help the United Colonies gain access to the Armistice Archives. The player can gain their consent - or not - and then access the Archives to collect the Terrormorph data Hadrian has requested and hopes will be the key to stopping the Terrormorphs.\n\nOne big note - this mission comes after a major Terrormorph attack on New Atlantis (deadly aliens) and so all the scenes should be informed by that. Folks are looking to act and make things right.

The player goes to Earth's Moon and discovers that the first grav-drive was developed with the help of NASA. Going to Earth, the player discovers that grav-drives caused the slow destruction of Earth's atmosphere, and that an Artifact was used to develop the first grav-drive.
Go on a radiant mission for Ryujin Industries to sabotage something that slows down their competitor.

Ryujin (and Imogene) is happy with the player's progress after completing three minor jobs (RIR01, RIR02, and RIR03) and wants to see how they do on a more visible, corporate level.  The player goes to the Trade Tower to the Astral Lounge to disrupt a deal between Infinity LTD and Quantum Synergies. They'll need sway the two Quantum Synergies executives, Zola Adisa and Arthur Cruz, against the deal with Infinity LTD, and then swap out Nina Hart's (the representative for Infinity LTD) presentation with a fabricated one.

The player has agreed to help Hadrian address the United Colonies Cabinet in hopes of getting access to their old Terrormorph research. The player can attempt to convince them to - or advice them against - opening the Armistice Archives, the respository of knowledge from the Colony War. \n\nJust as the decision is coming down, Terrormorphs attack the city. The player and Hadrian have to protect the city from the Terrormorphs rampaging around the spaceport. Once they have, they can return to the President, who informs them they've decided to help the player access the information they requested from the Archives.

The player has received their first mission with the Vanguard - deliver a few antenna on the distant world of Tau Ceti II - but get there to discover the entire settlement has been killed. There they meet, Hadrian, a former Xenowarfare researcher come to this world to find out how a Terrormorph got all the way here. The player and Hadrian take the Terrormorph down, at which point Hadrian makes a discovery - this Terrormorph appears to have come out of nowhere.

The player arrives in orbit around Oborum III, a planet orbiting a star in the Scorpius constellation. What they find is the Starborn ship, the Helix. The Starborn EMISSARY is having a meeting with the Starborn HUNTER. They are at first surprised the player is there, but invite them to join the meeting to discuss the Artifact hunt and reveal the secrets of the Starborn and the Unity.

The Red Mile is an outpost on the remote world of Porrima III. It used to be a den for thieves, pirates, smugglers, and cold-blooded killers alike, but now it's been cleaned up slightly and turned into a spectator sport attraction by its propreitor, Mei Divine. It still draws a rough crowd, but now everyone gathers at the bar overlooking a deadly obstacle course, where patrons gamble on whether brave competetors will make it through the course, or die trying.

The player has gotten into a massive flight sim and has to fight a series of simulated opponents of increasing difficulty. From the game's perspective, they're still in the same room they were before, but to the player it appears they're out in space. There are two main voices in this - the Exam Proctor - who's a real human who's voice has been recorded and is playing back outside the simulator, and the digital computer voice of the sim itself.
Go on a radiant mission to retrieve a security keycard.
NOEL puts together a memorial service for the Companion who dies when the Hunter attacked. Depending on who died, differrent people are in attendance.

[LC088 - Crimson Fleet Final Battle - Attack on Key]
[LC088 - Crimson Fleet Final Battle - Attack on Vigilance]
Shared Crime Lines across Unique Voicetypes

Summary: WALTER STROUD invites the player on a mission to Neon, a city run by wealthy corporations. He will be purchasing an Artifact there, and he wants the player as backup. Walter goes to his office on Neon and meets with ISSA EKLUND, his wife and business partner, to discuss the purchase. The player is then sent to investigate the seller and case the Astral Lounge, the meeting place, for security issues. The player then meets with the seller, MUSGROVE, and along with Walter negotiate for the purchase of the Artifact. On the way out from the meeting, the player is ambushed by agents hired by Slayton Aerospace, the original owner of the Artifact. The player has to infiltrate Slayton Aerospace HQ and confront its boss, NICOLAUS Slayton.
Go on an assignment to plant physical evidence at Laredo Firearms in Akila City.

The player has signed up to take the entrance exam of the Vanguard, the UC's civilian fleet. The player has to go through two tests - Adaptability (a series of obstacle courses) and Ship Piloting (which takes place inside a simulator).
This quest contains all the narration for the various UC Vanguard Orientation museum exhibits and the companion's responses to them.
Go on a radiant mission to upload something onto a terminal.

Returning from MQ202, the player finds out that the Eye, Constellation's star station, has been attacked. A Starborn who calls himself the Hunter has attacked the station, and is on his way to the Lodge. The player has to decide whether to run to the station to save those onboard, or defend the Lodge and the Artifacts.
This quest holds the radio scene that advertises the job available at Ryujin Industries to start the Ryujin Faction quest line.

This is the intro quest to the Ryujin Industries faction. The player hears an ad playing in either New Atlantis or Neon which starts the quest to apply for a job. After filling out the application at a computer kiosk, the player gets an interview with Imogene Salzo, attends the interview, and then gets their first task as an administrative assistant: go pick up a coffee order at the nearby TerraBrew.\n\nHowever, while picking up coffee, the player is held at gunpoint by a freshly fired employee. The employee believes it's just a matter of time before Ryujin sends the player after him, so he's trying to get a jump on things and take out the player before the player takes out him. The player can try to talk him down, or outright attack. Either way, the player resolves the situation, picks up the coffee order, delivers it, and then reports back to Imogene. Imogene, having heard of what the player did at TerraBrew, now sees greater potential in the player as more than just an administrative assistant which will launch the player into their new role in the next quest.

Summary: Actors player hasn't seen before recalc when they load in for the first time. This wipes our any data you might have set on them previously. Putting an actor in a Non-Start Game Enabled quest alias prevents that.\n\nSo for any actors you want to set data on player loads, can be put into the refcollection alias in this quest.
